# ============================================================
# LEARNOVA — .phaseupdate
# Phase-by-Phase Development Tracker
# ============================================================
# Update this file after completing each phase.
# Format: mark [x] when done, fill in actual completion date,
# and add any notes about deviations or issues encountered.
# ============================================================

LAST_UPDATED: 2026-03-21
CURRENT_PHASE: 0


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 0 — Project Setup & Foundation
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STATUS: [x] Complete (verify PostgreSQL credentials + `alembic upgrade head` locally)
COMPLETED_DATE: 2026-03-21

WHAT THIS PHASE DOES:
  Bootstraps the entire monorepo. Creates both the React frontend (Vite)
  and FastAPI backend from scratch, installs all dependencies, configures
  Tailwind + shadcn/ui, sets up PostgreSQL connection via SQLAlchemy,
  creates the base Alembic migration scaffold, and establishes environment
  variable handling. Also creates the health-check endpoint, the base
  Axios client with JWT interceptor, and the root routing structure.

HOW IT WORKS IN THE SYSTEM:
  - Frontend runs at http://localhost:5173
  - Backend runs at http://localhost:8000
  - Backend connects to local PostgreSQL (learnova database)
  - GET /api/v1/health returns { "status": "ok" } — verifies the stack is alive
  - CORS is configured to allow frontend to call backend
  - The Tailwind config imports custom color tokens matching the palette

DELIVERABLES:
  [x] frontend/ folder with Vite + React + TypeScript
  [x] Tailwind + shadcn/ui installed and configured
  [x] Color tokens configured in tailwind.config.ts
  [x] backend/ folder with FastAPI + SQLAlchemy + Alembic
  [ ] PostgreSQL connection working (learnova database exists) — set `DATABASE_URL` / password in `backend/.env`
  [ ] /api/v1/health endpoint responding — requires working DB (returns 503 if DB down)
  [x] Both .env.example files created
  [x] Base Axios client in src/services/apiClient.ts

ISSUES / DEVIATIONS:
  — `asyncpg` added alongside pinned `psycopg2-binary` so `AsyncEngine` works; Alembic uses sync `postgresql://` via env conversion.
  — Initial migration added manually (`a1b2c3d4e5f6_initial_empty.py`); re-run `alembic revision --autogenerate` after Phase 1 models if desired.
  — `components.json` + `src/lib/utils.ts` scaffold shadcn-style setup; run `npx shadcn@latest add …` to pull full UI primitives when needed.


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 1 — Authentication & User Management
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STATUS: [ ] Pending
COMPLETED_DATE: —

WHAT THIS PHASE DOES:
  Implements full auth: registration, login, JWT issuance, and a
  protected /me endpoint. Creates the users table in PostgreSQL.
  On the frontend: Login page, Register page, protected route wrapper,
  role-based route guard, and the global auth Zustand store.

HOW IT WORKS IN THE SYSTEM:
  - POST /api/v1/auth/register → creates user, returns JWT
  - POST /api/v1/auth/login    → validates credentials, returns JWT
  - GET  /api/v1/auth/me       → returns current user profile (requires token)
  - JWT is stored in localStorage (local dev)
  - Axios interceptor attaches Bearer token to every request
  - ProtectedRoute redirects to /login if no valid token
  - RoleRoute shows 403 if user role is not allowed
  - 3 seed users created: admin@learnova.com / instructor@learnova.com / learner@learnova.com

DATABASE TABLES CREATED:
  users (id UUID PK, email, password_hash, full_name, role, avatar_url,
         total_points, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at)

DELIVERABLES:
  [ ] users table migration (Alembic)
  [ ] /api/v1/auth/register, /login, /me endpoints
  [ ] Login page UI (email + password)
  [ ] Register page UI (name + email + password + role selector)
  [ ] Zustand authStore (user, token, login(), logout(), isAuthenticated)
  [ ] ProtectedRoute component
  [ ] RoleRoute component
  [ ] Seed script for 3 test users

ISSUES / DEVIATIONS:
  —


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 2 — Admin Course Dashboard (Kanban + List)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STATUS: [ ] Pending
COMPLETED_DATE: —

WHAT THIS PHASE DOES:
  Builds the instructor/admin course dashboard — the first page after login
  for admin/instructor roles. Displays all courses in either Kanban or List
  view. Includes search, a + button to create a new course via a small modal,
  and action menus (Edit / Share) on each course card.

HOW IT WORKS IN THE SYSTEM:
  - GET /api/v1/courses returns all courses for the authenticated instructor
  - Kanban view groups courses into columns (Draft / Published)
  - List view shows courses in a table
  - Create course modal: enter title → POST /api/v1/courses → redirect to edit form
  - Share: copies the learner-facing course URL to clipboard
  - Published badge shows if course is live on website

DATABASE TABLES CREATED:
  courses (id UUID PK, title, slug, tags[], cover_image_url, is_published,
           website, visibility, access_rule, price_cents, responsible_user_id,
           views_count, total_duration_seconds, created_by UUID FK,
           created_at, updated_at, deleted_at)

DELIVERABLES:
