# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 4 — Content Management (Lessons)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STATUS: [ ] Pending
COMPLETED_DATE: —

WHAT THIS PHASE DOES:
  Implements the Content tab inside the course form. Instructors can see
  a list of all lessons, add new ones via a 3-tab popup editor, edit or
  delete existing lessons. Supports three lesson types: Video, Document, Image.

HOW IT WORKS IN THE SYSTEM:
  - GET    /api/v1/courses/:id/lessons → list lessons
  - POST   /api/v1/lessons → create lesson
  - PUT    /api/v1/lessons/:id → update lesson
  - DELETE /api/v1/lessons/:id → soft delete
  - Video type: stores YouTube/Drive URL + duration
  - Document type: stores file reference + allow_download flag
  - Image type: stores file reference + allow_download flag
  - Lesson editor popup has 3 tabs: Content / Description / Attachments

DATABASE TABLES CREATED:
  lessons (id, course_id FK, title, type ENUM, video_url, file_url, duration_seconds,
           allow_download, description, sort_order, responsible_user_id,
           created_at, updated_at, deleted_at)
  lesson_attachments (id, lesson_id FK, type ENUM[file|link], url, label,
                      created_at)

DELIVERABLES:
  [ ] lessons + lesson_attachments migrations
  [ ] CRUD endpoints for lessons and attachments
  [ ] LessonList component (Content tab)
  [ ] LessonEditorModal (3-tab popup)
  [ ] VideoLessonForm / DocumentLessonForm / ImageLessonForm
  [ ] Delete confirmation dialog

