# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 6 — Course Options, Attendees & Publishing
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STATUS: [ ] Pending
COMPLETED_DATE: —

WHAT THIS PHASE DOES:
  Fills in the Options tab (visibility + access rules), and implements the
  Add Attendees and Contact Attendees wizards. Connects the publish toggle
  to the actual backend logic.

HOW IT WORKS IN THE SYSTEM:
  - Options tab: visibility (Everyone/Signed In), access (Open/Invitation/Payment)
  - When access=Payment: price field appears
  - Add Attendees wizard: enter email(s) → creates enrollment records → sends invite email
  - Contact Attendees wizard: compose subject + body → sends to all enrolled learners
  - Only published + visibility=Everyone courses appear on public catalog
  - Visibility=SignedIn: only logged-in learners see it
  - Access=Invitation: only enrolled learners can start the course

DATABASE TABLES CREATED:
  enrollments (id, user_id FK, course_id FK, enrolled_at, enrolled_by UUID FK,
               created_at)

