# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 11 — Quiz — Learner Side
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STATUS: [ ] Pending
COMPLETED_DATE: —

WHAT THIS PHASE DOES:
  Quiz experience inside the full-screen player. Intro screen → one question
  per page → proceed → final question shows Complete Quiz button. On completion,
  awards points based on attempt number and the quiz's reward config.

HOW IT WORKS IN THE SYSTEM:
  - GET /api/v1/quizzes/:id/intro → shows question count, attempt history
  - POST /api/v1/quizzes/:id/start → creates a new attempt record
  - POST /api/v1/quizzes/:id/submit → submits answers, returns score + points awarded
  - Points = reward_config[attempt_number] (capped at attempt_4plus after 4th try)
  - Zustand quizStore: stores current question index, selected options
  - On completion: quiz marked completed in sidebar (tick), points popup shown

DATABASE TABLES CREATED:
  quiz_attempts (id, user_id FK, quiz_id FK, attempt_number, score_percentage,
                 points_awarded, started_at, completed_at)
  quiz_answers (id, attempt_id FK, question_id FK, selected_option_ids[],
                is_correct)

DELIVERABLES:
  [ ] quiz_attempts + quiz_answers migrations
  [ ] GET /api/v1/quizzes/:id/intro
  [ ] POST /api/v1/quizzes/:id/start
  [ ] POST /api/v1/quizzes/:id/submit
  [ ] QuizIntroScreen component
  [ ] QuizQuestionPage component (one per page)
  [ ] Zustand quizStore with localStorage persist

