# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PHASE 14 — File Uploads & Storage
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
STATUS: [ ] Pending
COMPLETED_DATE: —

WHAT THIS PHASE DOES:
  Wires up actual file upload for: course cover images, document lessons,
  image lessons, and lesson attachments. Uses local /uploads folder for
  development (configured via STORAGE_TYPE=local in .env).

HOW IT WORKS IN THE SYSTEM:
  - POST /api/v1/uploads → receives multipart file, validates, saves, returns URL
  - Files saved as: /uploads/<uuid>.<ext>
  - GET /api/v1/uploads/:filename → serves file (with auth check for protected files)
  - Frontend useFileUpload hook handles upload progress state
  - Document viewer: embed PDF in iframe using the served URL
  - Image viewer: display image from served URL

DELIVERABLES:
  [ ] POST /api/v1/uploads endpoint (multipart, validation, uuid rename)
  [ ] GET /api/v1/uploads/:filename endpoint
  [ ] useFileUpload hook with progress state
